FIELD.name: separation
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Distance from master source to user source

FIELD.name: name
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source name in the format '2CXO Jhhmmss.s{+|-}ddmmss[X]'

FIELD.name: err_ellipse_r0
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Major radius of the 95% confidence level position error ellipse

FIELD.name: err_ellipse_r1
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Minor radius of the 95% confidence level position error ellipse

FIELD.name: err_ellipse_ang
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Position angle (ref. local true north) of the major axis of the 95% confidence level error ellipse

FIELD.name: significance
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Highest flux significance (S/N) across all stacked observations and energy bands

FIELD.name: likelihood_class
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Highest detection likelihood classification across all stacked observations and energy bands

FIELD.name: conf_flag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source may be confused (source regions overlap in one or more contributing stacked observations)

FIELD.name: sat_src_flag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source is saturated in all observations; source properties are unreliable

FIELD.name: streak_src_flag
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Source is located on an ACIS readout streak in all observations; source properties may be affected

FIELD.name: flux_aper_b
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events; ACIS broad (0.5-7.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: flux_aper_lolim_b
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events (68% lower confidence limit); ACIS broad (0.5-7.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: flux_aper_hilim_b
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events (68% upper confidence limit); ACIS broad (0.5-7.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: flux_aper_w
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events; HRC wide (~0.1-10.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: flux_aper_lolim_w
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events (68% lower confidence limit); HRC wide (~0.1-10.0 keV) energy band

FIELD.name: flux_aper_hilim_w
FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Aperture-corrected net energy flux inferred from the source region aperture, best estimate derived from the longest block of a multi-band, flux-ordered Bayesian Block analysis of the contributing observations, and calculated by counting X-ray events (68% upper confidence limit); HRC wide (~0.1-10.0 keV) energy band
